cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the analysis of Wikipedia articles in different languages, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques (cs.CL). It also involves the study of temporal evolution and cultural dimensions of the articles (cs.SI), as well as the comparison of article snapshots (cs.IR). The use of a web-based user interface suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and the visualization of data (cs.DL). Finally, the study of interlingual article similarity may also involve computational linguistics (cs.CY).
